modules.description: This module decodes and encodes HTTP timestamps to and from `Ptime.t`, supporting IMF, RFC 850, and asctime formats. It handles input and output for HTTP date strings used in headers like `Date` or `Last-Modified`, always interpreting timestamps in UTC. Functions include `decode` for parsing strings into time values, `encode` for converting time values to formatted strings, and `pp` for directly printing to a formatter.
